         <abstract>
            <p>The public assumes that, in attempting to maintain fair and orderly markets during the one-sided rush of orders following major world events, the exchange specialist suffers substantial losses. An analysis of the behavior of stock prices following such events suggests, however, that he usually makes a tidy profit.</p>
          </abstract>
